How to reproduce,

0) Get HTC One phone (happens on all generations I tested)
1) Download libgdx setup app, and create project using latest version
2) Create Stage like this (Or any other.) :

``` Java
public class MainStage extends Stage {

    public Image img;

    public MainStage() {
        super();
        Gdx.input.setInputProcessor(this);

        img = new Image(new Texture("badlogic.jpg"));
        addActor(img);
    }

    public void act(float delta) {
        img.setX(img.getX() + delta*100f);
        if(img.getX() > 100) {
            img.setX(0);
        }
    }
}
```

3) Run the application and push on stage with your 3 fingers simultaneously 20 times.

On further investigation, I can see that while touchDown is called for all 3 fingers, touchUp is not, thus pointers add up.

Strangely I noticed that similar bug was present a year ago, but then later fixed, so I do not know how it still happens. Here is the link to the [pull reuqest](../pull/1097) that was supposed to fix it.

**As it crashes, here is the part of stacktrace:**

_java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: length=20; index=20_
_at com.badlogic.gdx.scenes.scene2d.Stage.touchDown(Stage.java:261)_
_at com.badlogic.gdx.backends.android.AndroidInput.processEvents(AndroidInput.java:389)_

Here are the methods that turned out to be useful in one of my projects

``` java
    /** Convenience method to create a model with a single node containing a circle shape.
     * The resources the Material might contain are not managed, 
     * use {@link Model#manageDisposable(Disposable)} to add those to the model.
     * @param attributes bitwise mask of the {@link com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.VertexAttributes.Usage}, 
     * only Position, Color, Normal and TextureCoordinates is supported. */ 
    public Model createCircle(float radius, int divisions, int primitiveType, final Material material, final long attributes) {
        return createCircle(radius, divisions, primitiveType, 0, 360, material, attributes);
    }

    /** Convenience method to create a model with a single node containing a circle shape.
     * The resources the Material might contain are not managed, 
     * use {@link Model#manageDisposable(Disposable)} to add those to the model.
     * @param attributes bitwise mask of the {@link com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.VertexAttributes.Usage}, 
     * only Position, Color, Normal and TextureCoordinates is supported. */ 
    public Model createCircle(float radius, int divisions, int primitiveType, float angleFrom, float angleTo, final Material material, final long attributes) {
        begin();
        part("circle", primitiveType, attributes, material).circle(radius, divisions, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, angleFrom, angleTo);
        return end();
    }

    /** Convenience method to create a model with a single node containing an ellipse shape.
     * The resources the Material might contain are not managed, 
     * use {@link Model#manageDisposable(Disposable)} to add those to the model.
     * @param attributes bitwise mask of the {@link com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.VertexAttributes.Usage}, 
     * only Position, Color, Normal and TextureCoordinates is supported. */ 
    public Model createEllipse(float width, float height, float innerWidth, float innerHeight, int divisions, int primitiveType, float angleFrom, float angleTo, final Material material, final long attributes) {
        begin();
        part("ellipse", primitiveType, attributes, material).ellipse(width, height, innerWidth, innerHeight, divisions, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, angleFrom, angleTo);
        return end();
    }
```
